caption: Randomly walking around the local Korean market and found a stairwell that smelled great. Reading the signs I just had to explore it more and when I did I was hit by the massive amounts of food choices. Left Wing was my pick and their garlic chicken sandwich meal is a must get for those hankering an easily affordable, non-fast food chain chicken sandwich which is cooked fresh. I’m planning on eating the menu in the coming months so this place is a definite must try!
The chicken pieces were a bit thinner than I expected, but pretty filling and tasty regardless.

This place is BOMB. Best Korean-style chicken on Oahu. I love the flavors and it's always made fresh to order, but never felt that the order took long. Have always ordered the boneless, but recently noticed they added a sandwich and don on the menu. Excited to try them soon! If you don't like spicy, maybe stick with the chili soy sauce or original...you really can't go wrong.

Giving 3 stars due to lack of attention to details.  Ordered the small with the pickles as the choice of sides.  Ordered an addition side of pickles.  Order arrived with only 1 of the 2 sides.  Chicken was still the best had on island.  Just disappointment among group trying to share one rather than 2 sides of pickles.

(Translated by Google) I ate it raw and it was crispy and delicious! Two 20 pieces were good to eat and the seasoning was better than fried  (Original) 순살로 먹었는데 바삭하고 맛있었어요! 20피스 둘이 먹기 좋았고 후라이드보다는 양념이 괜찮았어요

It is a best chicken in Hawaii and great tasted Korean chicken!!! Very delicious and fresh. Well cooked, perfectly marinated. Reasonable price. Definitely going again. Staff was really chill, welcoming and attentive. If they are busy there might be delay in your order but that's obvious.

Absolutely delicious!  We got the Chili Soy Garlic Boneless Chicken.  The chicken was cooked perfectly, and the seasoning was excellent.  They added sautéed white and green onions, which added a nice texture and flavor.  I loved how it wasn’t too greasy or heavy, but still hit the fried chicken spot.  Best I have had in Honolulu, and will definitely be returning!
Best Korean Fried Chicken in Hawaii. Sweet&spicy and Chili soy garlic thoes 2flavors are $25 and pickle radish is free lol. It was so good. I will definitely come back !!
